Olá, antes de mais nada, iremos explicar qual o sentido de  Lenga-lenga .

O que queremos é uma roda de conversa, tipo um bate papo descontraído e sem preocupações. Pensando nisso pedimos aos nossos estudiosos para encontrar um nome, após dias de muita procura não conseguimos encontrar,  os melhores nomes já tinham sido usados ( Podpah ,  Flow  e  ticaracaticast ) foi uma surpresa ao ver que esses já foram usados. Quem diria né. 

 Ai entra nosso mega apresentador (Marcelo) em seu momento de lucidez  (devido a idade) relembrava a época de escola (sim, ele foi...)  ele se sentava ao fundo da sala de aula (já que era um rapazinho bem falador) para conversar com seus amigos e volta e meia a professora esbracejava para eles  Ei ai do fundo vão parar com essa lenga lenga aí? 
 Nesse momento nosso produtor perguntou o que era lenga lenga, nisso fomos procurar seu significado real, já que não era de nossa época e vimos que se tratava de  Nada mais do que conversa fiada ou conversa informal.
Somos un podcast joven 🎙️🎧🙋🏻‍♂️, estamos chiquitos por ahora pero hablaremos de cine, series y todo lo geek 🥰

راه باش تخرج نهائيا من المصفوفة ماشي شي حاجة ساهلة
و أصلا ماشي كلشي قادر يخرج، الغالب الله كانين بعض الناس غادي يبقاو تما.
فالأول غادي تصدم،
من بعد غادي دوز من مرحلة الغضب،
غادي تحاول ترجع للمصفوفة ماغديش تقدر،
غادي تحاول تتقبل الواقع ولكن ماشي بسهولة،
تقدر دوز أيام صعيبة، مثلا شوية ديال الأرق اليلي،
توتر، و تقدر توصل حتى الإكتئاب،
مع مرور الوقت ضروي تمر للمرحلة تقبل الواقع المر،
من بعد ماغديش تبقى تحس بالمرورة، غادي تحس بالحلاوة ديال الحكمة الرديبيلة ، ملي غادي تشوف الأغلبية ديال الناس مازال عايشين في غيبوبة، غادي تحاول تتكلم وتفيق الناس،
غادي تعاود ترجع الغضب، حقاش ماشي ساهل تفيق الناس، و هذا جزء لايتجزء من المصفوفة، و حتى هو واقع خاصك تتقبلو.
باش الأمور تبقى غادية مزيان خاصك ضروري ، تحافظ على الجرعة الأسبوعية، على الأقل بالنسبة للناس القدامى، اما الناس الجدد في عالم الريد بيل، ضروري من الجرعة اليومية، 
و متتوقفش على تطوير الذات، سوى كنتي جديد و لا قديم،
وللحديث بقية.
Porque ninguém é anônimo , todos temos uma história pra contar !

Late morning show egy dalról.
Vendégünk a zenekar, műsorvezető Csorba Lóci és Lévai Balázs.

A podcast története:
2020-ban Lóci megkérdezte Balázst, hogy nem lehetne-e folytatni a Dob + Basszust, ami a királyi televízión ment több mint tíz évvel ezelőtt, de egyfajta amerikai típusú rádiós műsorként. Balázs azt mondta, csak akkor, ha megmarad a nyomozás: ki lehet-e bontani egy dalból az együttes teljes történetét? Lóci pedig azt mondta, oké, de ahhoz ragaszkodom, hogy legyenek benne játékok! Egymás kezébe csaptak, vettek két mikrofont, és felhívták a kedvenc együtteseiket.

Nossa ideia é abordar assuntos diversos e extrair de nossos convidados histórias boas que precisam ser contadas de uma forma descontraída, não como uma entrevista e sim como um bate papo. Apresentado por Carlos Mafia, diretor de filmes publicitários com muitos anos de trás das câmeras, mas que diante delas é jovem aprendiz, assim como Rafael Guiso, um jovem talentoso que busca trazer reflexões a respeito dos assuntos abordados e trazer suas compreensões de acordo com sua idade..
Adoramos histórias motivacionais, cases de sucesso, desenvolvimento pessoal e as diversas áreas das artes. Inspirar e levar ao nosso público além do entretenimento conteúdo de relevância que colabore com o desenvolvimento da audiência.

 Nesse momento nosso produtor perguntou o que era lenga lenga, nisso fomos procurar seu significado real, já que não era de nossa época e vimos que se tratava de  Nada mais do que conversa fiada ou conversa informal.

و أصلا ماشي كلشي قادر يخرج، الغالب الله كانين بعض الناس غادي يبقاو تما.
فالأول غادي تصدم،
من بعد غادي دوز من مرحلة الغضب،
غادي تحاول ترجع للمصفوفة ماغديش تقدر،
غادي تحاول تتقبل الواقع ولكن ماشي بسهولة،
تقدر دوز أيام صعيبة، مثلا شوية ديال الأرق اليلي،
توتر، و تقدر توصل حتى الإكتئاب،
مع مرور الوقت ضروي تمر للمرحلة تقبل الواقع المر،
من بعد ماغديش تبقى تحس بالمرورة، غادي تحس بالحلاوة ديال الحكمة الرديبيلة ، ملي غادي تشوف الأغلبية ديال الناس مازال عايشين في غيبوبة، غادي تحاول تتكلم وتفيق الناس،
غادي تعاود ترجع الغضب، حقاش ماشي ساهل تفيق الناس، و هذا جزء لايتجزء من المصفوفة، و حتى هو واقع خاصك تتقبلو.
باش الأمور تبقى غادية مزيان خاصك ضروري ، تحافظ على الجرعة الأسبوعية، على الأقل بالنسبة للناس القدامى، اما الناس الجدد في عالم الريد بيل، ضروري من الجرعة اليومية، 
و متتوقفش على تطوير الذات، سوى كنتي جديد و لا قديم،
وللحديث بقية.

Podcast theGame je kreativno zabavni podcast koji će pratiti sportaše kroz njihovu karijeru.

Želja nam je pratit mlade sportaše na njihovom putu prema uspjehu, ali i vrhunske sportaše koji trenutno ostvaruju najsjajnije rezultate.
 Velik broj sportaša trenutno je ne prepoznato u našoj svakodnevnici i samim time kroz naše emisije mi žalimo približiti široj javnosti kako izgleda životni put sportaša.

Naše podcast sastajati će se od nekoliko oblika emisija kroz koje ćemo vam približiti:
1. Kako je to biti sportaš(upoznavanje sportaša), 
2. Što sve sportaši prolaze na svojem putu do uspjeha, 
3. Koliko je bitna zaštita njihovog zdravlja, 
4. Sa čime se hrane i što sve koriste od vitaminizacije,
5. Kako izgleda njihova svakodnevnica po završetku sportske karijere.

Uz sve naše teme ostavljamo dovoljno prostora i vama i nama za nove projekte i unaprjeđenje našeg zajedničkog rasta prema edukativno - zabavnom pocastu kroz vaše sugestije i prijedloge.

With an initial interest in IoT Security, the Podcast has grown into varying fields – from M2M, IIoT and Connected Devices – spanning the globe and promoting the excellent work of these companies, from start-ups to multinational businesses, there’s a real variety of people who have contributed so far to the series.

We would like to thank all those who have contributed so far to make the IoT Podcast what it is today and look forward to seeing this evolve over time.

Take an intimate look inside the minds of swimming's highest achievers with one of the world's best swim coaches, Brett Hawke.

As a swimmer, Brett swam in two Olympic Finals (2000, 2004) of the 50 Free. He never did quite break 22 seconds (22.07) but he did take a 100 Free out in 22.5 to his feet once. In college, he swam for Auburn University under legend David Marsh. He won the 50 Free at 1997 NCAA's in 19.19. 

After his pro swimming career, he became an Assistant Coach at Auburn University. At the 2008 Olympics in Beijing, he guided Cesar Cielo to victory in the Men's 50 Freestyle. Cesar's gold medal swim was the first in Brazil's history. In 2009, after the sudden passing of Richard Quick, Brett led an inspired team of Tigers through an emotionally charged NCAA's. 

Most recently, Brett helped guide Bruno Fratus to a Bronze medal in the Men's 50 Free at the Tokyo Olympics.

Iron Culture was started by Eric Helms and Omar Isuf as a means of exploring the world of physical culture and attempting to distill a unified philosophy of lifting and to help listeners find greater meaning from the iron. The lifting community has become fractured over the last ~70 years and this Podcast will attempt to explore the fundamental threads that unite these different tribes. The Podcast focuses on dispensing practical, useful information to the listener, bouncing from history, to philosophy, to contemporary lifting culture issues, to science. This can range from teaching the audience about lifting, programming, nutrition, supplements/PEDs and the history of lifting culture. The format includes casual conversations between the two hosts on a variety of topics, discussions with a panel of experts and interviews with authoritative figures in the lifting community.

On a cold December day in 2009, the mystery that still captivates America began.

Susan Powell was a regular woman. She was a wife, a mother, a co-worker, and church-goer.

She was also a victim, but of just what crime, no one can say with certainty.

She disappeared on a cold December night nearly 10 years ago. Her body has never been found.

KSL’s Dave Cawley has spent the last three years examining tens of thousands of documents and recordings relating to the case of Susan Powell. He's uncovered evidence that has never before been seen or heard publicly -- information that brings this haunting cold case into a whole new light, many times through the words of those involved.

Join Cold as we take a look inside the mind of Josh Powell, inside this fractured family, and inside this fateful marriage.

Why did Josh kill in cold blood? Why was he was never charged with a crime? And why did Susan never leave?

We’ve strived to answer these questions in this multi-part podcast, Cold.

در بی‌پلاس چه خبره؟
ما در بی‌پلاس کنجکاوی می‌کنیم، بیشتر هم برای اینکه سؤال‌های تازه‌تر و بهتری بپرسیم.

پادکست بی‌پلاس چی؟
پادکست فارسی بی‌پلاس از اردیبهشت 97 خلاصه‌ی کتاب‌های غیر داستانی تعریف می‌کنه.

کانال یوتیوب بی‌پلاس چی؟
اینجا ما می‌ریم دنبال کنجکاویهامون، هم پرسش‌های تازه، هم موضوعاتی که قبلاً تو پادکست ازشون حرف زدیم.
فعلا هر هفته دو ویدیوی جدید منتشر می‌کنیم.
اگر شما هم علاقه‌مند به این دست کنجکاوی‌ها هستید و دوست دارید ریز ریز کنار هم چیز یاد بگیریم یادتون نره کانال یوتیوب بی‌پلاس رو سابسکرایب کنید.

وبلاگ بی‌پلاس چی؟
تقریبا ساده و سرراست از همین کنجکاوی‌ها صحبت می‌کنیم و نویسنده مهمان هم داریم.

کتاب‌های معرفی شده در بی‌پلاس رو از کجا بخریم؟
در قسمت از کجا بخریم وبسایت می‌تونید به صورت آنلاین یا تلفنی تهیه کنید.

بهترین همراهی شما چی؟
برای هر کس که اهل این دست کنجکاوی‌ها و یادگرفتن‌هاست کانال بی‌پلاس رو بفرستید.
کنجکاوی جدید و محتوای خودتون رو بسازید.

Channel Description:
From a young age I took a route that most shy away from.  It was a journey that took me far from home, and far from the security that is invisible to many.  It was a journey rich in experiences, but I struggle to make sense of them.  They changed how I view the world, and those living in it.

If I am being honest, I struggle to make sense of most human behavior.  I try not to say much in public because I hold vastly different beliefs than most I encounter.  I sit back in awe of what comes out of some people’s mouths.

This podcast was born from curiosity.  I have nothing but questions about the world around me.  I constantly question what I think, and what I believe.

Ideas, discussions, and interviews with men and women on how to achieve a more fulfilling, successful life, when feelings of frustration, failure, overwhelm, and being stuck become your focus.
I know firsthand how this feels, having watched my 20 plus year career and life savings go up in smoke when I was fired from the company, I co-founded a decade earlier. After being stuck for years I started a personal development journey spanning years and thousands of hours of teachings from some good and not so good teachers. Over time I was able to disregard what didn't work and take only the best, most effective tools and assembled them into a streamlined process which helped me start getting results. I got myself back in shape, dropped 50lbs., back on a business track, out of debit, aligned spiritually, and reconnected with my family on a much deeper level. My Goal: I want you to feel as good as I do!
